        <title xml:id="spp-298-06E2-title-1">Upon the H<hi rend="small-caps">ORRID </hi>P<hi rend="small-caps">LOT</hi> dicovered by<lb/>  H<hi rend="small-caps">ARLEQUIN</hi>, the Bishop of R<hi rend="small-caps"><lb/>OCHE- STER</hi>'s French dog<ref target="#spp-298-06E2-footnote-title-1">1</ref><note n="1" xml:id="spp-298-06E2-footnote-title-1" place="foot">See the proceedings in parliament against Dr Atterbury the Bishop of Rochester. State-trials, vol. 6.── He was tried by the Lords for a plot against the government, deprived of his bishoprick, banished his native country, and died in France, Feb. 15. 1732</note>.</title>
